(95,	1,	'2020-01-20 09:20:49',	'2020-01-20 09:20:49',	'<!-- wp:casinotoplist/article-top-content {\"title\":\"Free Slots Online - Play Slots without Spending a Cent\",\"description\":\"So many slots, so little time! If youre a lover of Online Slots, then you dont need us to tell you that there are so many different kinds of slots that you could get into! Here at CasinoToplists, we are experts in all kinds of slots, and we plan to make you slots experts too by the end of this column! First things first though\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:casinotoplist/casino-toplist {\"heading\":\"Best Online Casinos 2019\",\"group_id\":\"2\",\"quantity\":\"5\",\"show_term_link\":\"yes\",\"term_text\":\"dfgdfgdfg\",\"term_link\":\"https://www.casinotoplists.com/casino-games/online-blackjack\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>Ever wondered where your favorite casino game came from?</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Slot machines can be found not only in live casinos, but also online at virtual casinos (and McCarran Airport in Las Vegas). However, these popular machines have a very humble history. The slot machine\'s story began at the turn of the 20th Century, when a German immigrant named August Fey built a metal box with three spinning reels in San Francisco. The three reels contained various symbols, including bells, and when three bells lined up in the box\'s window, the top prize was awarded. The idea caught on quickly, and less than a decade later, Herbert Mills in Chicago expanded upon the \"Bell Machines,\" adding symbols and widening the window so players who missed hitting could see just how close they came to a winning spin. Mills mass-produced his machines and sold them all over the country. Initially, these machines paid in prizes other than cash to avoid gambling legislation, but in 1931 when gambling was legalized in Nevada, cash-payout slots quickly began to appear in local casinos. In 1960, the Bally\'s company replaced the traditional mechanical make-up of the slot machine with an electromechanical system; this allowed for machines that could both collect and pay out faster and quickly made Bally\'s the market leader in slot machines. Today, slot machines often have a tremendous amount of bells and whistles, even more than before. While some still have the \"arm\" that can be cranked to set the wheels in motion, they can all be operated simply by pressing a button on the display. They allow for multiple coins that can result in payouts on as many as nine lines, and offer huge progressive jackpots. Furthermore, the slot revolution has moved to the online world. When online casinos began cropping up at the turn of the 21st Century, slot machines were a natural addition. They operate in almost exactly the same way as their physical counterparts, with no need to lug heavy buckets of coins to a cashier window. As casino gambling has evolved, slot machines have evolved and their popularity as a gaming option shows no sign of waning.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:casinotoplist/casino-toplist {\"group_id\":\"2\",\"quantity\":\"2\",\"style\":\"mini-rows\",\"show_supported_casino\":\"no\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>The Classic Slot</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is one that normally contains three reels rather than the 5-reel we are more used to. Classic slots were the first slots to go online. They normally portray the traditional slot symbols that first come to mind when you think casino slots. They have less paylines than the 5-reel ones, however they still offer a good selection of bonuses and fun play. If you like to keep it traditional and simple classic slots are definitely the ones you should go for! You\'ll recognize the most traditional slot machine design which features colorful fruits and inviting buzzing sounds. At CasinoToplists.com, you can play this classic slot machine game for free by heading to our Free Slots online page.</p>\n<!